01/12/2005
PRISTINA, Kosovo, Serbia-Montenegro -- The UN-managed Kosovo Trust Agency announced on Wednesday (30 November) that it would offer 15 companies for sale to private bidders as part of its so-called 11th privatisation round. 
The firms include the province's only sunflower oil producer, a brick maker, a pipe factory and two hotels.
In other news Wednesday, NATO denied that its base in Kosovo, Camp Bondsteel, was used as a secret prison. 
A spokesman said the facility meets all international standards and people detained in it have regular access to visitors and lawyers. 
(AP - 30/11/05)
